parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine misfiring and failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially at high speeds.
Broken manifold bolts can cause engine misfiring and failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the rear hatch or lift gate can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety hazards, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: Rear hatch or lift gate will not open with key pad or from inside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause various problems, including lift gate, lift rear glass, and acceleration issues, which can lead to accidents or inconvenience.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corroded brake lines and leaks can cause brake fluid to leak, leading to a loss of brake pressure, which can result in extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floorboard
brake pedal must be pumped extensively to stop the vehicle
grinding noise when applying the brakes
service stability light illuminates on the instrument panel.
